Also seeing `aihub-upsell.spec.ts` fail: `model-confidence-upsell-btn` isn’t found since `showCommercialUpsell` is `false` for some reason
https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/16187/overview/a8628e63-1d96-4a5f-91d2-[…]y?att=1&roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1733765275534 (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/16187/overview/a8628e63-1d96-4a5f-91d2-f3ccb9dab260/replay?att=1&roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1733765275534)

i’d recommend logging into crafting-cyp as site admin -> deleting this user -> rerun CI?

unless @Xindi Xu you have a better suggestion?
i think just rerunning CI could work. We create a new community user by adding it to the org and then removing it. Probably the removing step errored

I think it’s using `CyUser.DEFAULT` & isn’t changing between reruns since it’s happened 3 times in a row now:
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/65872

`aihub-upsell` is logging in as <mailto:cypress-user-65872@instabase.com|cypress-user-65872@instabase.com>

but yes, i agree nothing has changed between reruns since the test failed for the same reason in the latest rerun (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/16194/test-results/67f2e586-bb46-4b5f-8239-2ae42f24dccd?actions=%5B%5D&browsers=%5B%5D&groups=%5B%5D&isFlaky=%5B%5D&modificationDateRange=%7B%22startDate%22:%221970-01-01%22,%22endDate%22:%222038-01-19%22%7D&orderBy=EXECUTION_ORDER&oses=%5B%5D&specs=%5B%7B%22label%22:%22apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/BuildApp/aihub-upsell.spec.ts%22,%22value%22:%22%5B%5C%22f07fe9bc-c6a0-4323-a0f9-9b2171e5ebbc%5C%22%5D%22%7D%5D&statuses=%5B%5D&testingTypesEnum=%5B%5D)
`CyUser.DEFAULT` is mapping to `cypress-user-<pr number>` if it's not using the preexisting users.
OK. Try removing the user from the org manually

based on the code, it seems that we don’t try to re-create the user from scratch on reruns if the user exists

so i think we need to manually remove this user from the `cypress-drive-tests` org
i logged in using the “Cypress CI Drives” credentials on 1password and removed this user
the same error should not occur if `aihub-upsell` is rerun @Liam Callanan
